{
  "description": "A large, weathered rock is the focal point, covered in a dense cluster of dark, barnacle-like organisms on its lower portion. The rock\u2019s upper surface is a light, mottled gray, suggesting age and exposure to the elements. A narrow strip of sandy beach separates the rock from the blue-green ocean in the background. The barnacles create a textured, almost organic pattern around the base of the rock, contrasting with the smoother, more monolithic form of the stone itself. The lighting appears to be soft, indicating possibly an overcast day or the late afternoon.",
